{"rows": [{"updated": "2018-04-25T16:22:25.697444+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-3"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[2]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[2]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 551, "endOffset": 658}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 62424, "start": 62317}, {"exact": "he understood himself as a perpetrator and inextricably a part of the violence unleashed by the Apache crew", "prefix": " Although he made it clear that ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": ",\n52\n describing McCord as an \u2018e"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/bB8JuvyJEee8ozfxSL2pBA", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/bB8JuvyJEee8ozfxSL2pBA", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/bB8JuvyJEee8ozfxSL2pBA/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Source Excerpt:**\n\n\"We are both soldiers who occupied your neighborhood for 14 months...\n\nWe acknowledge our part in the deaths and injuries of your loved ones as we tell Americans what we were trained to do and carried out in the name of \u201cgod and country\u201d. The soldier in video said that your husband shouldn\u2019t have brought your children to battle, but we are acknowledging our responsibility for bringing the battle to your neighborhood, and to your family. We did unto you what we would not want done to us.\"\n\n**Full Citation:** Courage to Resist, \u2018Letter of reconciliation and responsibility to the Iraqi People\u2019, Courage to Resist (2010), available at: http://www.couragetoresist.org/news/838-letter-of-reconciliation-and-responsibility-to-the-iraqi-people.html (defunct; archived version <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20111010144910/http://www.couragetoresist.org/news/838-letter-of-reconciliation-and-responsibility-to-the-iraqi-people.html\">here</a>).", "created": "2018-01-18T19:54:40.650850+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019"]}, "id": "bB8JuvyJEee8ozfxSL2pBA", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-25T16:19:37.631338+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec1"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/p[3]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/p[3]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 196, "endOffset": 379}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 32126, "start": 31943}, {"exact": "On 5 April 2010, gun sight footage from a United States Apache AH64 helicopter, leaked by Chelsea Manning to the whistleblowing organisation WikiLeaks, was made public on the Internet", "prefix": "opter in Baghdad, Iraq in 2007. ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": " along with stills from the foot"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/SAJnuPyMEeeP90_7ccfjEw", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/SAJnuPyMEeeP90_7ccfjEw", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/SAJnuPyMEeeP90_7ccfjEw/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:**\nThe Collateral Murder web site consists of:\nAn overview page with three embedded videos. This contains both a longer and a shorter, edited, version of the Apache footage and a video of a US soldier, Ethan McCord speaking at a peace conference:https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/\n\nA page containing download links for videos and associated transcripts: https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/en/download.html\nA page containing a set of stills taken from the video: https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/en/stills.html\nA page containing a timeline of events depicted in the video:https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/en/timeline.html\nA page containing a transcript of the video: https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/en/transcript.html\nA page containing further resources, including US military rules of engagement for the time of the incident, news sources from the time of the incident, photos and captions relating to the two Reuters employees who were killed, and 'New Iraqi Material' which consists of subsequently added details concerning the children injured in the attack and their father who was killed: https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/en/resources.html\n\nThere are two further webpages, one containing details of how to support WikiLeaks and one containing contact details: \n\nhttps://wikileaks.ch/support.html (defunct; archived copy <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110209102403/https://wikileaks.ch/support.html\">here</a>)\n\nhttps://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/en/contact.html\n", "created": "2018-01-18T20:15:08.764087+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019"]}, "id": "SAJnuPyMEeeP90_7ccfjEw", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-24T18:38:23.148955+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "selector": [{"endContainer": "/section[4]/div[1]/div[1]/h1[1]", "startContainer": "/section[4]/div[1]/div[1]/h1[1]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 0, "endOffset": 111}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 1982, "start": 1871}, {"exact": "Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019", "prefix": "t;\n              }\n            \n", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": "\n\n\n\n\n\n    var coreReaderAccess ="}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/YNTJZPyOEee4KDMI-tDX0w", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/YNTJZPyOEee4KDMI-tDX0w", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/YNTJZPyOEee4KDMI-tDX0w/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<br>\nThis is an Annotation for Transparent Inquiry project, published by the <a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu\">Qualitative Data Repository</a>.\n\n<br/>\n\n<strong><font>The <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5064/F643DB5O\">Data Overview</a> discusses project context, data generation and analysis, and logic of annotation.</font></strong>\n</br/> \n\nPlease cite as:\n\nTidy, Joanna. 2018. \"Data for: Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019\". Qualitative Data Repository. https://doi.org/10.5064/F643DB5O\n\n\nLearn more about ATI <a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/ati\">here</a>.\n", "created": "2018-01-18T20:30:09.593792+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019"]}, "id": "YNTJZPyOEee4KDMI-tDX0w", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-18T18:42:25.500899+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-1"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[7]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[7]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 851, "endOffset": 1013}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 51020, "start": 50858}, {"exact": "when communications from the ground-based clean-up team alert the crew to the presence of injured children in the fired-upon vehicle, the crew are recorded saying", "prefix": " and enemy others. For example, ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": " \u2018well, it\u2019s their fault for bri"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/Xs_wHPyJEee04-dJiXORSw", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/Xs_wHPyJEee04-dJiXORSw", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/Xs_wHPyJEee04-dJiXORSw/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** The additional quotes below, taken from the video transcript (at https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/en/transcript.html ) are further, but not exhaustive, examples:\n\n04:31  Oh, yeah, look at those dead bastards.\n\n04:36  Nice.\n\n10:11  Oh yeah, look at that. Right through the windshield!\n\n10:14  Ha ha!\n\n18:29  I think they just drove over a body.\n\n18:31  Hey hey!\n\n18:32  Yeah!", "created": "2018-01-18T19:54:18.637397+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019"]}, "id": "Xs_wHPyJEee04-dJiXORSw", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-18T16:39:58.476490+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-3"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[4]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[4]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 998, "endOffset": 1073}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 66349, "start": 66274}, {"exact": "But in his \u2018eyewitness account\u2019 he also recalled seeing an RPG at the scene", "prefix": "im of his own son and daughter. ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": ", a departure from the long lens"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/NvGo4PyLEeewjqeN5QTnBA", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/NvGo4PyLEeewjqeN5QTnBA", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/NvGo4PyLEeewjqeN5QTnBA/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Source Excerpt:** Transcript extract at 7:38: \"I saw an RPG next to one of the men and an AK47.\"\n\n**Full Citation:** 'WikiLeaks' Collateral Murder: U.S. Soldier Ethan McCord's Eyewitness Story', embedded at: https://collateralmurder.wikileaks.org/", "created": "2018-01-18T20:07:30.647657+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019"]}, "id": "NvGo4PyLEeewjqeN5QTnBA", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-18T16:37:55.578295+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-3"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[5]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[5]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 322, "endOffset": 495}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 67447, "start": 67274}, {"exact": "McCord was quoted being critical of WikiLeaks and emphasising that both long lens cameras and RPGs were present something he felt had been obscured in their initial account.", "prefix": "te however. In media interviews ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": "\n57\n Writing McCord as an authen"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/uaoXXvyLEeeXKEMLe334Vw", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/uaoXXvyLEeeXKEMLe334Vw", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/uaoXXvyLEeeXKEMLe334Vw/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Source Excerpt:**\n'However, when I did come up on the scene, there was an RPG as well as AK-47s there\u2026. You just don\u2019t walk around with an RPG in Iraq, especially three blocks away from a firefight\u2026. Personally, I believe the first attack on the group standing by the wall was appropriate, was warranted by the rules of engagement. They did have weapons there.'\n\n**Full Citation:** Zetter, \u2018U.S. soldier on 2007 Apache attack\u2019.", "created": "2018-01-18T20:11:09.901017+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019"]}, "id": "uaoXXvyLEeeXKEMLe334Vw", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-18T16:34:43.038573+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-3"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[5]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[3]/p[5]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 1, "endOffset": 200}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 67152, "start": 66953}, {"exact": "The video of McCord\u2019s testimony on the WikiLeaks website includes his statement that he saw an RPG amongst the bodies, and this was acknowledged explicitly by Julian Assange in later media interviews", "prefix": " audience could identify with.\n ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": ".\n56\n WikiLeaks maintained the e"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/dn319PyLEeeMoB-OIzntIw", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/dn319PyLEeeMoB-OIzntIw", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/dn319PyLEeeMoB-OIzntIw/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Source Excerpt:**\nJulian Assange, a WikiLeaks editor, acknowledged to Fox News in an interview Tuesday evening that \"it's likely some of the individuals seen in the video were carrying weapons.\" \n\nAssange said his suspicions about the weapons were so strong that a draft version of the video they produced made specific reference to the AK-47s and RPGs. Ultimately, Assange said, WikiLeaks became \"unsure\" about the weapons. He claimed the RPG could have been a camera tripod, so editors decided not to point it out. \n\n\"Based upon visual evidence I suspect there probably were AKs and an RPG, but I'm not sure that means anything,\" Assange said. Nearly every Iraqi household has a rifle or an AK. Those guys could have just been protecting their area.\"'\n\n**Full Citation:** Fox News, \u2018Military raises questions about leaked Iraq shooting video\u2019.\n", "created": "2018-01-18T20:09:17.438641+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experience-rewriting-war-from-above-in-wikileaks-collateral-murder/C114DD6B918FF7274AC5B6E071139F93/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Visual regimes and the politics of war experience: Rewriting war \u2018from above\u2019 in WikiLeaks\u2019 \u2018Collateral Murder\u2019"]}, "id": "dn319PyLEeeMoB-OIzntIw", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-11T17:08:34.100027+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/review-of-international-studies/article/visual-regimes-and-the-politics-of-war-experien